article.headline: Sacred Heart 58, Lehigh 56
article.story: FAIRFIELD, Conn. (AP) -- Center Kibwe Trim capitalized on a missed shot by Omar Wellington with 7.5 seconds left to lead Sacred Heart to a 58-56 win against Lehigh Saturday. Sacred Heart (2-1) led 32-29 at halftime, but blew a 7-point lead late in the second half when Lehigh (1-2) rallied. Lehigh's Austen Rowland scored five points and Jose Oliverio had a three to narrow the score at 56-56 with 14 seconds left. Wellington's shot fell short, but Trim grabbed the ball out of the air and dunked it to give the Pioneers the lead. Oliverio's last 3-point attempt bounced off the rim. James Samuels led Sacred Heart with 21 points. Trim finished with 12 points. Rowland led the Mountain Hawks with 19 points.
